verse.lines:
{lang-eng}I come to the garden alone,
While the dew is still on the roses;
And the voice I hear,
Falling on my ear;
The Son of God discloses.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}I’d stay in the garden with Him
Tho’ the night around me be falling,
But He bids me go;
Thru the voice of woe,
His voice to me is calling.{/lang-eng}
